(8, '{\"en_GB\":\"Privacy Policy\",\"ar\":\"\\u0627\\u0644\\u0635\\u0641\\u062d\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062f\\u064a\\u0646\\u0627\\u0645\\u064a\\u0643\\u064a\\u0629\"}', 'privacy-policy-new-style', '{\"en_GB\":\"<h1>How can I get a privacy policy on my website? A GDPR compliant privacy policy<\\/h1><p><br><\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">The privacy policy can be written as an independent page on your website, and be made accessible as a link in the header or footer of your website, or on your \\u2018About\\u2019 page. It may also be hosted by a privacy policy-service with a link from your homepage.<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">Basically, it doesn\\u2019t matter where you choose to place it, as long as your users have access to it.The privacy policy is a legal text. The phrasing depends on which jurisdictions your website falls under and how&nbsp; website handles data.<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\"><br><\\/p><h1 style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\"><b>All websites are different. We always recommend that you consult a lawyer to ensure that your privacy policy is compliant with all applicable laws.&nbsp;<\\/b>However, this might seem as a large expense if you are, for instance, a hobby blogger or small business.<\\/h1><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">What you should&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/@StartupPolicy\\/five-reasons-why-copying-someone-else-s-terms-of-use-and-privacy-policy-is-a-bad-idea-fd8d126ac0b3\\\">never do, is to copy a privacy policy from some other website<\\/a>.<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">That is also why using a privacy policy generator can be a hazardous thing, since you must be very careful to include all the specific information of your website, and not just have privacy policy generator spit out a default one that isn\'t aligned with your domain<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\"><br><\\/p><h5>GDPR <b>privacy policy templates &amp; privacy policy generators<\\/b><\\/h5><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">There exists numerous tools for creating privacy policies, and privacy policy templates and privacy policy generators on the internet.<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">Some are free and others come at a price. Some are not GDPR compliant privacy policies.<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\"><br><\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">1) Maintain all the content properly<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">2) Ensure your all input is right<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\">3) if you can do multiple task that will be plus<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-size:16px;color:rgb(22,34,42);font-family:Gotham, sans-serif;\\\"><br><\\/p><p style=\\\"font-family: Gotham, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(22, 34, 42);\\\">There policy is the numerous tools for creating privacy policies, and privacy policy templates and privacy policy generators on the internet. Some are free and others come at a price. Some are not GDPR compliant privacy policies.<\\/p><p style=\\\"font-family: Gotham, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(22, 34, 42);\\\"><br><\\/p><p style=\\\"font-family: Gotham, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(22, 34, 42);\\\"><b>Note :&nbsp;<\\/b>just have privacy policy generator spit out a default one that isn\'t aligned with your domain So it\'s very important loyal technical theury of our reservation.<